data-emotion="css 1ucudpe">.css-1ucudpe{display:-webkit-box;display:-webkit-flex;display:-ms-flexbox;display:flex;-webkit-align-items:center;-webkit-box-align:center;-ms-flex-align:center;align-items:center;min-height:inherit;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;text-align:center;}</style><div class="MuiBox-root css-1ucudpe"><style data-emotion="css 1sl8dhm">.css-1sl8dhm{-webkit-box-flex:1;-webkit-flex-grow:1;-ms-flex-positive:1;flex-grow:1;width:100%;}</style><div class="MuiBox-root css-1sl8dhm" data-testid="id/article/slide/5252490/element/4/ad" id="article-25252490-ad_rect_atf_01-1"></div></div></div><div class="MuiBox-root css-6emr8c" id="id/article/slide/5252490/element/5"><p class="MuiTypography-root MuiTypography-bp_small__body__article__medium css-1vqr2el">Tomlin was speaking about the way a veteran backup can bring some "intangible components" to the game in a way that a less experienced quarterback is unable to do because they haven't yet learned to do that in the NFL.</p></div><div class="MuiBox-root css-6emr8c" id="id/article/slide/5252490/element/6"><p class="MuiTypography-root MuiTypography-bp_small__body__article__medium css-1vqr2el">In the game that Tomlin is referencing from Week 4 last season, the Steelers weren't exactly stopping Richardson before he left the game late in the first quarter due to a shoulder injury.</p></div><div class="MuiBox-root css-6emr8c" id="id/article/slide/5252490/element/7"><p class="MuiTypography-root MuiTypography-bp_small__body__article__medium css-1vqr2el">The Colts were already up 7-0 and Richardson got them into Steelers territory on their second offensive possession when the injury occurred. Joe Flacco finished off that drive with a four-yard touchdown pass to Josh Downs.</p></div><div class="MuiBox-root css-6emr8c" id="id/article/slide/5252490/element/8"><p class="MuiTypography-root MuiTypography-bp_small__body__article__medium css-1vqr2el">Indianapolis went on to beat the Steelers 27-24, with Flacco finishing 16-of-26 for 168 yards and two touchdowns. It's worth noting Richardson was 3-of-4 for 71 yards and had 24 rushing yards in just 13 plays.</p></div><div class="MuiBox-root css-6emr8c" id="id/article/slide/5252490/element/9"><p class="MuiTypography-root MuiTypography-bp_small__body__article__medium css-1vqr2el">The strategy behind Tomlin's comment was sound. Richardson completed 49.3 percent of his attempts with twice as many interceptions (six) as touchdowns (three) in his first three starts before the Steelers game.</p></div><div class="MuiBox-root css-6emr8c" id="id/article/slide/5252490/element/10"><p class="MuiTypography-root MuiTypography-bp_small__body__article__medium css-1vqr2el">It's entirely possible that if Richardson had played the entire game, he would have eventually turned back into the player he was in the first three weeks.</p></div><div class="MuiBox-root css-6emr8c" id="id/article/slide/5252490/element/11"><p
